==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Desmognathous
<hw>Des*mog"na*thous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>desmo`s</grk> bond + <grk>gna`qos</grk> jaw.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the maxillo-palatine bones united; --
applied to a group of carinate birds (<ord>Desmognath⟦ae⟧</ord>),
including various wading and swimming birds, as the ducks and herons,
and also raptorial and other kinds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Desmoid</ent>⟦br⟧
